                            <td style="width: 50%; padding: 0 30px;">
                                <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 0; margin-left: 0;">
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                    <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">1. What is a Decreasing Term Assurance (DTA)? </span>
                                    A DTA is an insurance cover provided by most insurance companies which will cover the outstanding balance on your loan account in the event of death or permanent disability. The cover limit of the DTA reduces as the loan debt reduces.
                                </li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                    <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">2. Who is eligible for this coverage? </span>
                                    Customers who avail of a loan facility with the bank and where the DTA is required as part of the loan's terms and conditions.
                                </li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                    <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">3. What is the scope of of a DTA Cover?</span>
                                    <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 0; margin-left: 0;">
                                        <li style="font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                            (a) Death
                                        </li>
                                        <li style="font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                            (b) Total and Permanent Disability (TPD)
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p style="font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                        In the event of death or TPD, your family is protected from the burden of repaying your loan. The Insurance company shall settle the outstanding balance on the loan account less any arrears.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                    <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">4. When does the coverage start?</span>
                                    Coverage under the DTA typically commences on the date the loan is disbursed.
                                </li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                    <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">5. When does the coverage end?</span>
                                    <ul style="padding-left: 30px;">
                                        <li style="list-style-type: disc;">On expiry of the term of the policy</li>
                                        <li style="list-style-type: disc;">If a claim benefit is paid out for death or totaldisability</li>
                                        <li style="list-style-type: disc;">On early settlement or full prepayment of the loan facility</li>
                                        <li style="list-style-type: disc;">If the policy has lapsed due to non-payment of the premium</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <div style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;"><span style="font-weight: 800;">Note:</span>The above list is NOT exhaustive and may vary according to your insurance policy.</div>
                                </li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                    <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">6. Does the DTA cover have a surrender/maturity value?</span>
                                    There is no surrender value linked to a DTA. No lump sum is payable to the customer at the end of the coverage.
                                </li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                    <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">7. What if I pre-pay the loan – do I get any refund?</span>
                                    Yes. Upon early settlement or full repayment of the loan, premiums (net of any charges) may be paid on a pro-rata basis by the insurance company, based on the unexpired term of the policy. Terms and conditions apply.
                                </li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                    <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">8. Do I need to renew the policy? (where applicable)</span>
                                    Yes. Renewal of the policy on the due date is under your responsibility and will be deducted directly from your account.  Please ensure that sufficient funds are available on your account to cater for the premium payment.
                                </li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                    <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">9. Are there any waiting/deferred periods to claim for benefits under polices?</span>
                                    <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 30px;">
                                        <li>(i) Death - No waiting/deferred period</li>
                                        <li>(ii) TPD - 6 months waiting period / deferred period</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                    <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">10. Is there a commission which is earned by the bank which is acting as an Insurance agent when providing this service on Insurances?</span>
                                    As an Insurance Agent, the Bank  is an intermediary for the Insurance company for which is it licensed and will earn a commission based on this relationship. The commission earned by the bank varies from products to products and is disclosed in the policy documents remitted to the customer upon issuance of the policy.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                            </td>
                            <td style="width: 50%; padding: 0 30px;">
                                <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 0; margin-left: 0;">
                                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                        <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">11. What is the claim process?</span>
                                        In the event of death or TPD, the borrower or his legal representative should immediately advise the bank at the nearest branch.  The following documents should be submitted:

                                        <ul style="padding-left: 30px; list-style-type: disc;">
                                            <li>A claim form, duly completed and signed.</li>
                                            <li>Original customer’s Identification document, e.g., Passport, Driver’s Licence, National Identity Card</li>
                                            <li>Death: Original Death Certificate and/or Medical Certificate stating the cause and occurrence of death ( in event of Death)</li>
                                            <li>TPD: Original medical certificate (in the event of TPD)</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </li>
                                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                        <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">12. What are general claims exclusions under this policy?</span>
                                        This will depend on the insurance policy, provided by your chosen insurance provider.  You are advised to refer terms and conditions of the prefered Insurance provider.
                                    </li>
                                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                        <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">13. What is your responsibility when applying for a DTA cover?</span>
                                        Your true and correct declaration is crucial when enrolling for any insurance. We believe in your good faith to provide us with all required information and to highlight any additional information that will impact on the assessment effected by your chosen Insurance Company. 
                                    </li>
                                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 8.2pt;">
                                        <span style="font-weight: 800; display: block; font-size: 7.2pt; line-height: 8pt; margin-bottom: 5px;">14. Which Insurance Companies provide(s) DTA cover via Absa Bank (Mauritius) Ltd?</span>
